<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-01-13T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-01-13T21:00:00-05:00" n="798" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/808: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Chefoo</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Roberts</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chefoo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-01-14T10:00:00+08:00">January
                                    14, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received January 14—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3. 1. Chefoo Harbor Office recently organized by the Japanese Navy
                            announced that effective January 15 it will take over from the Chinese
                            Maritime Customs: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“(1), Supervision of pilotage; (2), assignment of berths; (3),
                                    control harbor and all vessels entering and leaving it; (4),
                                    supervision of quarantine; (5), notifications concerning the
                                    harbor; (6), communication with vessels.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>2. Masters of vessels are required to deliver on arriving to harbor
                            boarding officer arrival report, passenger list, crew list and import
                                <pb facs="0808" n="804" xml:id="pg_804"/> manifest and on departing
                            to the Chefoo Harbor Office clearance application, passenger list and
                            export manifest.</p>
                        <p>3. Shanghai please inform Commander in Chief.<note n="39" xml:id="d798fn39">Adm. Harry E. Yarnell, U. S. Asiatic Fleet.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping, Tsingtao and Chungking.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Roberts</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>